						               													<description>A Leader of Men is a miniature wargame capturing Company-level combat in WW2 and more recent wars. It uses a new and unique system to remove a high degree of control from players, but allows them to play the role of Leaders trying to direct and control the battle situation. Players will get intensely involved in the game as the battles developed and are shaped by the Leaders the player represents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules include all you need to start playing except for the equipment listed in the rules, miniatures, and scenery.  The book is 118 pages in an A4 format.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;middot; Rules covering combat during WW2 with many helpful examples of play, guides, and thoughts on the application.&amp;#10;&amp;middot; Six generic scenarios for two players.&amp;#10;&amp;middot; A solo play scenario.&amp;#10;&amp;middot; A guide to major armies in Europe during WW2.&amp;#10;&amp;middot; A selection of Army lists for the major combatants with individual Army Quick Reference Sheets.&amp;#10;&amp;middot; A Quick Reference page for the rules.&amp;#10;&amp;middot; Army List note pages to record the important details of your army in an easy to use format.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
